page.title: 17Housing-Downsview area
page.content: This is a non estate area with roads of mainly semi-detached houses built ither in the 30's or in the 50's.We did see 1 pre-victorian house and 2 victorian houses. We talked to a lady who told us that the houses in Marse Way were all about 40years old.Next we went up Rogers Court,there were 10 flats and 12 terraced houses built during 60's to 80's.There were 6 bungalows and 6 houses in South view,the road went up and down hills.The gardens were well looked after with lovely gardens. We saw a house that we thought was very old but the owner told us that it was much younger.
